			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Low-Health Aggro Kiting (Cross-Posted from SOE boards)<a name="72402"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 24 05 7:29 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>(Some guy was talking about some people using low-health aggro to AE the entire second field in Plane of Fire in a single shot.  The runner was a SK, and there were 5 wizards.  I made this post, and I figured I might as well share it with you all.)
<br />

<br />

<br />
Ok, confession time:
<br />

<br />
I have, in the past, attempted to exploit low-health aggro.  This was after our extended-range AA's were nerfed, but before our PBAoE songs were nerfed to uselessness.  Along with another bard, we tried using low-health aggro as a kiting technique, where he would constantly keep his health under 20% while running a bunch of mobs in a circle, and I would run behind him and play my PBAoE songs.  We tried this in HoH A.
<br />

<br />
It didn't work.
<br />

<br />
Oh, it sort of did.  You could do quite a bit of damage to these mobs, but at around every 30% of health loss, aggro changed from them to me.  I managed to bypass this by using Fading Memories, but my mana pool was too small to do more than a single kite of this, and with my bardic mana regen being as pathetic as it was, this kiting method was unsustainable.
<br />

<br />
In other words, low-health aggro is not infinite.  Granted, it takes a crazy amount of aggro to taunt a mob off (Those AE songs weren't just damage, they had debuff components), and it's certainly possible that 5 wizards working together could use this tactic to kill a LOT of mobs, but the risks would be extreme.  If the person being chased has a single freeze frame, the game is up, he gets flattened.  If he mis-times a turn, or pathing isn't quite what he expects, he'll get torn to pieces.  Bottom line, it's possible, but it takes a lot of very specific circumstances, including a substantial amount of luck, to work.  One slip, and the group wipes.  
<br />

<br />
Incidentally, the true BUG behind the old tactics faction war exploit was never fixed.  If you aggro a mob over 55 in any zone, and then another mob kills it, you will get the full xp.  This was originally done in order to address a problem that some raids had when &quot;ally&quot; mobs would KS a raid target, leaving the raid nothing for all their work (a la 10th ring war in Great Divide).  This can still be done in Maiden's Eye, between the static Goronga camps and the hooded guys.  You have to get the hooded guys to cast one of their AE jobbies in the viscinity of a Goronga, and voila!  Faction war.  Only problem is, the gorongas are so spread-out, and so much can happen to you between the camps, that it's not workable like the Tactics exploit was (so you could use this to kill maybe 3-4 mobs, after a LOT of very dangerous and risky work).  Frankly, you could just kill the mobs in ME faster.  I wouldn't be surprised if there's an OOW or DoN zone waiting to be exploited this way.  Time will tell.
<br />

<br />
Anyways... AE groups have been around a LONG time.  This tactic may seem unfair because it is so effective, and because it can disrupt a zone, but frankly I don't see that as being the fault of the players.  SoE has never regarded AE groups as being against the rules, nor have they considered aggro kiting to be illegal.  This is simply a logical combination of the two.  If SoE is ok with these tactics, then the problem is that their server cannot handle the load.
<br />

<br />

<br />
(Summarizing: I think a bard bellowing himself down with the level 12 song to keep his health low, and working with 5 AEing wizards, could take down a CRAPLOAD of very high-level, tough mobs, provided that none of them cast or summon.  Haven't tried this, though)</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=601903">Feroce</a> <br> 
Battle Bard, Grandmaster Smith, and Tradeskill Officer of Molto Espressivo, the All-Bard Guild of Firiona Vie</span></td>
