				<td colspan="2"><span>I agree, I don't see something like this an exploit.  I believe an exploit would have to be something someone does to alter the gameplay just for their own or other people's benefit.  Yes this is method benefits the people doing the kiting, but they did not alter or change the gameplay or coding or such to help themselves.  They (you) are just using what sony already gave us.  Now I do believe Sony has the right to say &quot;hey you are not suppose to be able to do that&quot; and they have ever right to change the code so you can't do it anymore, but they don't have the right to suspend accounts or anything to that nature.  Sony tests is suppose to test everything before it goes live, so if a player finds a bug and uses it to their advantage then they should feel fine with what they are doing, but if the player creates the bug, then they should be punished for altering the gameplay.  
<br />

<br />
Just my 2 cents.</span></td>
